rns) then it leaves no corpse and gives no exp.  <br><br>Small guilds with one or two manaburn enabled wizards would still be able to help out in Kunark encounter.  Wait until that dragon hits 49%, and burn away.<br><br>It would still be useful to take down normal mobs immediately, when you absolutely positively have to stop that CHing cleric mob.<br><br>The only thing that would change is that 'Team Manaburn' would be unable to farm dragons for loot.<br><br>All the legitimate(to me, at least) uses of manaburn are preserved.<br><br>Perhaps in compensation, have manaburn scale slightly based on a mob's total HP.  Nothing astronomical, maybe 25% higher or so on mobs with hundreds of thousands of hitpoints.<br><br>Are there any ramifications of this I missed?  Any suggestions?  While I know changing manaburn is not a subject popular among most wizards, it seems that Verant has a tendency to wildly overcompensate whenever they perceive a problem in balance.  So, it's better that sensible changes to submitted to them, before VI decides to make Manaburn castable only on moss snakes. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utargonis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Targonis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/1/02 12:37:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=738.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A sensible Manaburn change, and a request for comments</span><hr size=1> 7 to 9k damage on a full bar of mana for a level 60 wizard is weak enough.  I can see them nerfing CRIT ability on manaburn, but to eliminate the ability to use manaburn on ANY mob below a certain level is pathetic.  What, I can't kill a 7k mob once every now and then because they are worried?  How about a group of melees who take down a Kunark dragon in under a minute with their Velious weapons?  Can we get a nerf for them too, like no weapon that's more powerful than what's in Kunark can work in Kunark zones?<br>Yea, let's nerf priceless/primal armor, and in Kunark zones, all melees get at most a 30 percent haste total, regardless of upgrades.<br> <p>Targonis Manastorm<br>Level 60 Wizard<br>The First Seal<br>The Nameless Server<br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udecorbin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Decorbin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/1/02 10:04:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=738.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.webdeveloper.com/animations/bnifiles//lightnin.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A sensible Manaburn change, and a request for comments</span><hr size=1> Nerfing MB is a terrible choice to make, if VI desides to do it.  MB isn't useable every 10 min or even every hour...it's every 2.5 ours (appox). It's not like the Velium weapons, primal armor, etc. that can be used constantly during every encounter. IMHO MB isn't anymore unbalanceing then the rogues Assassinate or the Rangers Endless Quiver.  <br><br>As far as changing it, I think it should stay the way it is.<br><br>VI don't nerf the MB. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ubenibus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Benibus</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/2/02 12:12:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=738.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A sensible Manaburn change, and a request for comments</span><hr size=1>   Ok when you see a group of rogues or Rangers taking a Dragon down to farm White Scales. Or Rage Fire to farm Cleric Epics(Mind you Porting in to KS it with a group of 6) then you have a have a valid arguement with the facts as you have stated it. As it stands now it is beyound rediculious I have a friend who has been after a white scale for I would guess atleast a year. Didn't want to pay for it to begin with but now he is even willing to pay for it and can't find a person willing to sell one for less then 35k(He was willing to pay 25). <br>  Pure and simple there needs to be a change atleast into regards of Epic creatures.My guild has had a team of Mana Burners Port in and KS us on Ragefire once. Oh so Very very fun and fair that after 7 days of a guild camping a zone that 6 people should be able to port in at a moments notice and KS you. If you don't see a problem there then you are just thinking selfish. This doesn't even effect me personally really,but since MB has came out no Kunark dragon lasts more then minutes on my server and that is just wrong! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utigertailz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>tigertailz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/2/02 2:34:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=738.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Good idea</span><hr size=1> and you could include that any high end mob hit with more than 50% of damage by melees will drop nothing <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>that way wizards will be welcome in groups...<br><br>what a fine idea. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udecorbin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Decorbin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/2/02 4:40:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=738.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.webdeveloper.com/animations/bnifiles//lightnin.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A sensible Manaburn change, and a request for comments</span><hr size=1> Benibus look at the whole picture.  How many wizards have manaburn?  How many people are in Uber guilds?  I can say with certanty, not a ton - unless you are on Legends.  The whole picture is that MB is only used by wiz 59 or 60 and with 27 AA points.  My guild took down RF last week and we don't have a single MB wiz.  There is a world of play before MB and after. Is it some people's fault that they have MB and use it? No.  Instead of gaining lvl's and better equip etc, we should just eliminate MB?  Come on.  Highlvl warrior and rogues can put out a extreme amount of damage on a constant basis, and Paly's can do it to undead.  With the Rangers Deadeye AA and unlimited quiver, i've seen them deal awesome damage also.  Should these classes get there damage reduced? or have Primal items removed from the game?  No.  And I don't think we should have MB eliminated either. This is my opinion, you have yours.<br><br>Edited for spelling. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udecorbin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Decorbin</A> at: 7/2/02 5:38:52 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=t